{
  "texts": [
    "Replace clusters C p and C q by C p ∪ C q, and store the new union maskM (C p ∪ C q) = M (C p) ∪ M (C q) ∪ M ({s, s ′ }).",
    "Stop when the next best merge would violate the union mask ratio thresholdτ ∈ [0, 1], min i̸ =j ϕ(C i, C j) > τ L. Time complexity.",
    "Calculating ϕ(C i, C j) is O(L), since M (C i)and M (C j) are stored, and only M (s, s ′) must be computed.",
    "In each merging step, computing all costs ϕ is O(n 2 L).",
    "Using a heap over cluster pairs, the final time complexity is O(n 2 log n + n 2 L)."
  ]
}